<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,438,789]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,225,618,644]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">Notes.</emphasis>
We re-instate 
<taxonomicName authority="Betrem, 1928" authorityName="Betrem" authorityYear="1928" box="[383,872,618,645]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosicola" subGenus="Discolia">
<emphasis box="[383,712,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">Scolia (Discolia) formosicola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Betrem, J. G." box="[717,872,618,645]" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" pagination="1 - 388" refId="ref13005" refString="Betrem, J. G. (1928) Monographie der Indo-Australischen Scoliiden mit zoogeographischen Betrachtungen. Treubia, 9 (Supplement), 1 - 388." type="journal article" year="1928">Betrem, 1928</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, as a valid species; it is distinctly different from the similar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1911" box="[236,347,654,681]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis box="[236,347,654,681]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">S. oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following: the dorso-median area of the propodeum is strongly and densely punctate (only superficially and sparsely punctate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1911" box="[582,696,690,717]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis box="[582,696,690,717]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">S. oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); vertex and frons with dense coarse punctation (largely smooth, without large punctures in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1911" box="[450,562,726,753]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis box="[450,562,726,753]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">S. oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and median groove of frons distinct (median groove of frons indistinct in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="116">S. oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
